The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Call more, get phone 

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Nov. 9: Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited (BSNL) today announced that it would soon introduce schemes for high-end customers and provide broadband services.

 We are going to provide free phones to existing landline customers who have paid an average monthly bill of Rs 1,500 or more in the last six months. They will have the option to choose between fixed line, cordless or mobile handsets against a monthly insurance of Rs 20. However, call charges will apply, BSNL chief general manager S.K. Chakraborty said.

 BSNL is also working on a technology Resilient Packet Ring to provide an additional rent-free landline for broadband services to existing landline or broadband customers.




